When a comment with children is deleted it would be less confusing if children were deleted too rather than moved up one level.

As admin-user I prepared a Global Template starting with 

{excerpt}
Example-Excerpt
{excerpt}

But as well when previewed and when saved the Template displays an NullPointerException which occurred in the macro.

I assume that it does not harm to the system, so this issue might even be Trivial rather than Minor.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-3896].
  {panel}

More and more useful information is being stored within the content property sets, so may well be time to add them to the Remote API.

Ideally there should be options for both AND and OR matches, defaulting to OR

{blog-posts:labels=confluence,jira|match-labels=any} (default, match-labels unnecessary here)
{blog-posts:labels=confluence,announcement|match-labels=all}

Example:

{rss:url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/syndication/feeds/news/ukfs_news/world/rss091.xml\|max=5} 
{rss:url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/syndication/feeds/news/ukfs_news/world/rss091.xml\ } 

See CSP-1290 for the original problem report.


The tailing '\' should not cause the macro to be ignored by the parser.

